{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I was only four years old"},{"time":2000,"text":"when I saw my mother load a washing machine"},{"time":5000,"text":"for the very first time in her life."},{"time":8000,"text":"That was a great day for my mother."},{"time":10000,"text":"My mother and father had been saving money for years"},{"time":13000,"text":"to be able to buy that machine,"},{"time":15000,"text":"and the first day it was going to be used,"},{"time":17000,"text":"even Grandma was invited"},{"time":19000,"text":"to see the machine."},{"time":21000,"text":"And Grandma was even more excited."},{"time":24000,"text":"Throughout her life"},{"time":26000,"text":"she had been heating water with firewood,"},{"time":28000,"text":"and she had hand washed laundry"},{"time":30000,"text":"for seven children."},{"time":32000,"text":"And now she was going to watch"},{"time":35000,"text":"electricity do that work."}]},{"cues":[{"time":38000,"text":"My mother carefully opened the door,"},{"time":42000,"text":"and she loaded the laundry"},{"time":44000,"text":"into the machine,"},{"time":46000,"text":"like this."},{"time":48000,"text":"And then, when she closed the door,"},{"time":50000,"text":"Grandma said, \"No, no, no, no."},{"time":52000,"text":"Let me, let me push the button.\""},{"time":56000,"text":"And Grandma pushed the button,"},{"time":58000,"text":"and she said, \"Oh, fantastic!"},{"time":61000,"text":"I want to see this! Give me a chair!"},{"time":63000,"text":"Give me a chair! I want to see it,\""},{"time":65000,"text":"and she sat down in front of the machine,"},{"time":68000,"text":"and she watched the entire washing program."},{"time":72000,"text":"She was mesmerized."},{"time":74000,"text":"To my grandmother,"},{"time":77000,"text":"the washing machine was a miracle."}]},{"cues":[{"time":80000,"text":"Today, in Sweden and other rich countries,"},{"time":83000,"text":"people are using"},{"time":85000,"text":"so many different machines."},{"time":87000,"text":"Look, the homes are full of machines."},{"time":89000,"text":"I can't even name them all."},{"time":91000,"text":"And they also, when they want to travel,"},{"time":94000,"text":"they use flying machines"},{"time":97000,"text":"that can take them to remote destinations."},{"time":99000,"text":"And yet, in the world, there are so many people"},{"time":101000,"text":"who still heat the water on fire,"},{"time":104000,"text":"and they cook their food on fire."},{"time":107000,"text":"Sometimes they don't even have enough food,"},{"time":109000,"text":"and they live below the poverty line."},{"time":112000,"text":"There are two billion fellow human beings"},{"time":115000,"text":"who live on less than two dollars a day."},{"time":117000,"text":"And the richest people over there --"},{"time":119000,"text":"there's one billion people --"},{"time":121000,"text":"and they live above what I call the \"air line,\""},{"time":125000,"text":"because they spend more than $80 a day"},{"time":128000,"text":"on their consumption."}]},{"cues":[{"time":130000,"text":"But this is just one, two, three billion people,"},{"time":133000,"text":"and obviously there are seven billion people in the world,"},{"time":136000,"text":"so there must be one, two, three, four billion people more"},{"time":139000,"text":"who live in between the poverty and the air line."},{"time":142000,"text":"They have electricity,"},{"time":145000,"text":"but the question is, how many have washing machines?"},{"time":148000,"text":"I've done the scrutiny of market data,"},{"time":151000,"text":"and I've found that, indeed,"},{"time":153000,"text":"the washing machine has penetrated below the air line,"},{"time":156000,"text":"and today there's an additional one billion people out there"},{"time":159000,"text":"who live above the \"wash line.\""},{"time":162000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":164000,"text":"And they consume more than $40 per day."},{"time":168000,"text":"So two billion have access to washing machines."}]},{"cues":[{"time":171000,"text":"And the remaining five billion,"},{"time":173000,"text":"how do they wash?"},{"time":175000,"text":"Or, to be more precise,"},{"time":177000,"text":"how do most of the women in the world wash?"},{"time":180000,"text":"Because it remains hard work for women to wash."},{"time":184000,"text":"They wash like this: by hand."},{"time":187000,"text":"It's a hard, time-consuming labor,"},{"time":191000,"text":"which they have to do for hours every week."},{"time":194000,"text":"And sometimes they also have to bring water from far away"},{"time":197000,"text":"to do the laundry at home,"},{"time":199000,"text":"or they have to bring the laundry away to a stream far off."},{"time":203000,"text":"And they want the washing machine."},{"time":206000,"text":"They don't want to spend such a large part of their life"},{"time":209000,"text":"doing this hard work"},{"time":211000,"text":"with so relatively low productivity."},{"time":213000,"text":"And there's nothing different in their wish"},{"time":215000,"text":"than it was for my grandma."},{"time":217000,"text":"Look here, two generations ago in Sweden --"},{"time":220000,"text":"picking water from the stream,"},{"time":222000,"text":"heating with firewood and washing like that."},{"time":225000,"text":"They want the washing machine in exactly the same way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":228000,"text":"But when I lecture to environmentally-concerned students,"},{"time":231000,"text":"they tell me, \"No, everybody in the world cannot have cars and washing machines.\""},{"time":236000,"text":"How can we tell this woman"},{"time":238000,"text":"that she ain't going to have a washing machine?"},{"time":240000,"text":"And then I ask my students,"},{"time":242000,"text":"I've asked them -- over the last two years I've asked,"},{"time":244000,"text":"\"How many of you doesn't use a car?\""},{"time":246000,"text":"And some of them proudly raise their hand"},{"time":248000,"text":"and say, \"I don't use a car.\""},{"time":250000,"text":"And then I put the really tough question:"},{"time":252000,"text":"\"How many of you"},{"time":254000,"text":"hand-wash your jeans and your bed sheets?\""},{"time":256000,"text":"And no one raised their hand."},{"time":259000,"text":"Even the hardcore in the green movement"},{"time":262000,"text":"use washing machines."}]},{"cues":[{"time":264000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":268000,"text":"So how come [this is] something that everyone uses"},{"time":270000,"text":"and they think others will not stop it? What is special with this?"},{"time":273000,"text":"I had to do an analysis about the energy used in the world."},{"time":276000,"text":"Here we are."},{"time":278000,"text":"Look here, you see the seven billion people up there:"},{"time":280000,"text":"the air people, the wash people,"},{"time":282000,"text":"the bulb people and the fire people."},{"time":285000,"text":"One unit like this"},{"time":287000,"text":"is an energy unit of fossil fuel --"},{"time":290000,"text":"oil, coal or gas."},{"time":292000,"text":"That's what most of electricity and the energy in the world is."},{"time":296000,"text":"And it's 12 units used in the entire world,"},{"time":299000,"text":"and the richest one billion, they use six of them."},{"time":302000,"text":"Half of the energy is used by one seventh of the world's population."},{"time":305000,"text":"And these ones who have washing machines,"},{"time":307000,"text":"but not a house full of other machines,"},{"time":309000,"text":"they use two."},{"time":311000,"text":"This group uses three, one each."},{"time":313000,"text":"And they also have electricity."},{"time":315000,"text":"And over there they don't even use one each."},{"time":318000,"text":"That makes 12 of them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":320000,"text":"But the main concern"},{"time":322000,"text":"for the environmentally-interested students -- and they are right --"},{"time":325000,"text":"is about the future."},{"time":327000,"text":"What are the trends? If we just prolong the trends,"},{"time":330000,"text":"without any real advanced analysis, to 2050,"},{"time":333000,"text":"there are two things that can increase the energy use."},{"time":336000,"text":"First, population growth."},{"time":338000,"text":"Second, economic growth."},{"time":340000,"text":"Population growth will mainly occur among the poorest people here"},{"time":343000,"text":"because they have high child mortality"},{"time":345000,"text":"and they have many children per woman."},{"time":347000,"text":"And [with] that you will get two extra,"},{"time":349000,"text":"but that won't change the energy use very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":351000,"text":"What will happen is economic growth."},{"time":354000,"text":"The best of here in the emerging economies --"},{"time":356000,"text":"I call them the New East --"},{"time":358000,"text":"they will jump the air line."},{"time":360000,"text":"\"Wopp!\" they will say."},{"time":362000,"text":"And they will start to use as much as the Old West are doing already."},{"time":365000,"text":"And these people, they want the washing machine."},{"time":368000,"text":"I told you. They'll go there."},{"time":370000,"text":"And they will double their energy use."},{"time":372000,"text":"And we hope that the poor people will get into the electric light."},{"time":375000,"text":"And they'll get a two-child family without a stop in population growth."},{"time":377000,"text":"But the total energy consumption"},{"time":379000,"text":"will increase to 22 units."},{"time":381000,"text":"And these 22 units --"},{"time":384000,"text":"still the richest people use most of it."},{"time":388000,"text":"So what needs to be done?"},{"time":390000,"text":"Because the risk,"},{"time":392000,"text":"the high probability of climate change is real."},{"time":395000,"text":"It's real."},{"time":397000,"text":"Of course they must be more energy-efficient."},{"time":400000,"text":"They must change behavior in some way."},{"time":402000,"text":"They must also start to produce green energy,"},{"time":404000,"text":"much more green energy."},{"time":406000,"text":"But until they have the same energy consumption per person,"},{"time":409000,"text":"they shouldn't give advice to others --"},{"time":411000,"text":"what to do and what not to do."},{"time":413000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":415000,"text":"Here we can get more green energy all over."}]},{"cues":[{"time":419000,"text":"This is what we hope may happen."},{"time":421000,"text":"It's a real challenge in the future."},{"time":424000,"text":"But I can assure you that this woman in the favela in Rio,"},{"time":427000,"text":"she wants a washing machine."},{"time":429000,"text":"She's very happy about her minister of energy"},{"time":432000,"text":"that provided electricity to everyone --"},{"time":434000,"text":"so happy that she even voted for her."},{"time":437000,"text":"And she became Dilma Rousseff,"},{"time":439000,"text":"the president-elect"},{"time":441000,"text":"of one of the biggest democracies in the world --"},{"time":443000,"text":"moving from minister of energy to president."},{"time":446000,"text":"If you have democracy,"},{"time":448000,"text":"people will vote for washing machines."},{"time":450000,"text":"They love them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":454000,"text":"And what's the magic with them?"},{"time":456000,"text":"My mother explained the magic with this machine"},{"time":459000,"text":"the very, very first day."},{"time":461000,"text":"She said, \"Now Hans,"},{"time":463000,"text":"we have loaded the laundry."},{"time":465000,"text":"The machine will make the work."},{"time":467000,"text":"And now we can go to the library.\""},{"time":469000,"text":"Because this is the magic:"},{"time":471000,"text":"you load the laundry,"},{"time":473000,"text":"and what do you get out of the machine?"},{"time":475000,"text":"You get books out of the machines,"},{"time":478000,"text":"children's books."},{"time":480000,"text":"And mother got time to read for me."},{"time":482000,"text":"She loved this. I got the \"ABC's\" --"},{"time":484000,"text":"this is where I started my career as a professor,"},{"time":487000,"text":"when my mother had time to read for me."},{"time":489000,"text":"And she also got books for herself."},{"time":491000,"text":"She managed to study English"},{"time":493000,"text":"and learn that as a foreign language."},{"time":495000,"text":"And she read so many novels,"},{"time":497000,"text":"so many different novels here."},{"time":500000,"text":"And we really, we really loved this machine."}]},{"cues":[{"time":504000,"text":"And what we said, my mother and me,"},{"time":507000,"text":"\"Thank you industrialization."},{"time":510000,"text":"Thank you steel mill."},{"time":512000,"text":"Thank you power station."},{"time":514000,"text":"And thank you chemical processing industry"},{"time":517000,"text":"that gave us time to read books.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":519000,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":521000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}